# Parallel dispatch (mandatory)

When planning or executing a batch, classify issues per [linear-delivery-workflow.mdc](./linear-delivery-workflow.mdc):

| Class | Meaning |
|-------|---------|
| **P** | Parallel-safe — no dependency on sibling in-flight work |
| **S** | Sequential — wait for upstream issue merge |
| **B** | Blocker — resolve before anything else |

---

## Rule

**If 2 or more issues in the current batch are class P and their dependencies are satisfied, the parent agent MUST launch Task subagents for ALL of them in a SINGLE message.**

Do **not** serialize parallel-safe work. Do **not** implement P-class issues one-by-one when they could run concurrently.

Reference flowchart: [docs/engineering/lifecycle-session-planning.png](../../docs/engineering/lifecycle-session-planning.png)

---

## Examples (Career Forge)

| Batch | Parallel group | Issues |
|-------|----------------|--------|
| Sprint 1 Foundation | **[P]** | HAC-5, HAC-6, HAC-7 (after HAC-19 done) |
| Sprint 5 Stretch | **[P]** | HAC-13, HAC-14, HAC-15 (after Sprint 4) |

Sequential chains (do **not** parallelize):

- HAC-8 → HAC-18 → HAC-9 (Sprint 2)
- HAC-10 → HAC-11 → HAC-12 (Sprint 4)

---

## Parent agent checklist

1. Read [docs/SPRINT-BOARD.md](../../docs/SPRINT-BOARD.md) or [docs/ROADMAP.md](../../docs/ROADMAP.md) for `[P]` markers
2. Confirm deps merged on `main`
3. Set all issues → `In Progress` via Linear MCP
4. Launch **one message** with multiple `Task` tool calls (one per issue)
5. After all subagents return: consolidate, run triple gate per branch, merge sequentially, update STATUS once

---

## Anti-patterns

- ❌ Implementing HAC-5, then HAC-6, then HAC-7 serially when all three are P
- ❌ Waiting for one P issue to fully merge before starting another P issue in the same batch
- ❌ Launching subagents in separate turns when they could have been parallel

